won't separate them again!

00:13:09.039 --> 00:13:09.998 position:50% align:center
[MANAGER A]
Hm?

00:13:10.081 --> 00:13:11.791 position:50% align:center
He's right!
They belong together!

00:13:11.875 --> 00:13:13.084 position:50% align:center
You wouldn't keep
a young man

00:13:13.168 --> 00:13:14.961 position:50% align:center
from his long-lost mother's
side, would you?

00:13:15.045 --> 00:13:18.882 position:50% align:center
You moron. Haru was just
making up a stupid story.

00:13:18.965 --> 00:13:20.675 position:50% align:center
He's gonna laugh in your faces.

00:13:20.759 --> 00:13:22.135 position:50% align:center
[MOMIJI]
...his mom left him,

00:13:22.218 --> 00:13:24.137 position:50% align:center
even though she really
didn't want to.

00:13:24.220 --> 00:13:26.556 position:50% align:center
But then...

00:13:26.639 --> 00:13:28.266 position:50% align:center
[MANAGER A]
Tragic.

00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:29.476 position:50% align:center
Yet touching. Ah!

00:13:29.559 --> 00:13:31.770 position:50% align:center
I don't know the last
time I was so moved.

00:13:31.853 --> 00:13:35.398 position:50% align:center
Him, too?! Is everyone
around here an idiot?

00:13:38.151 --> 00:13:39.903 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
I'm takin' my break.

00:13:39.986 --> 00:13:41.363 position:50% align:center
[COWORKER A]
Okay.

00:13:43.573 --> 00:13:45.742 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
It's so hot out here.

00:13:45.825 --> 00:13:48.703 position:50% align:center
I hope the rest of them
found someplace cool to--

00:13:51.206 --> 00:13:52.332 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:54.084 --> 00:13:56.127 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
No way. Is that--?

00:13:56.211 --> 00:13:57.879 position:50% align:center
I think...

00:13:57.962 --> 00:13:59.589 position:50% align:center
Got you!

00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:07.055 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
It's him.

00:14:09.474 --> 00:14:11.601 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
He's really here!

00:14:14.521 --> 00:14:16.856 position:50% align:center
[KURENO]
You're that girl from the store.

00:14:16.940 --> 00:14:18.400 position:50% align:center
That's me.

00:14:18.483 --> 00:14:22.404 position:50% align:center
Pretty funny... us running into
each other again like this.

00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:25.490 position:50% align:center
Are you okay? You look
a little worn out.

00:14:25.573 --> 00:14:27.075 position:50% align:center
Just catching my breath.

00:14:27.158 --> 00:14:28.910 position:50% align:center
I saw you walking
up ahead of me

00:14:28.993 --> 00:14:31.204 position:50% align:center
and I didn't wanna
lose you, so, uh,

00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:34.082 position:50% align:center
I started sprinting
for all I was worth.

00:14:34.165 --> 00:14:35.125 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI laughs]

00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:37.002 position:50% align:center
Sounds kinda crazy, huh?

00:14:37.085 --> 00:14:38.336 position:50% align:center
Man, it's hot.

00:14:38.420 --> 00:14:41.131 position:50% align:center
[stomach growls]

00:14:41.214 --> 00:14:43.049 position:50% align:center
Do you need something to eat?

00:14:43.133 --> 00:14:45.468 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Yeah, I haven't had lunch yet.

00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:49.681 position:50% align:center
Crap, I'll get majorly hangry
if I don't get food in me soon.

00:14:49.764 --> 00:14:51.850 position:50% align:center
I could use some lunch, too.

00:14:51.933 --> 00:14:55.437 position:50% align:center
We should go somewhere
together. My treat.

00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:56.730 position:50% align:center
You serious?

00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:58.189 position:50% align:center
I owe you one.

00:14:58.273 --> 00:15:00.775 position:50% align:center
After the mess I made
at the store that night.

00:15:00.859 --> 00:15:03.194 position:50% align:center
Oh, hell yeah!
Wait for me, <i>tororo</i> soba!

00:15:03.278 --> 00:15:04.654 position:50% align:center
I'm comin' for ya!

00:15:04.738 --> 00:15:07.407 position:50% align:center
Um. Nothing fancier, maybe?

00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:10.243 position:50% align:center
Ha! All I want these
days is <i>tororo</i> soba.

00:15:10.326 --> 00:15:12.662 position:50% align:center
Start thinkin' about what
you wanna order. Ha!

00:15:12.746 --> 00:15:14.998 position:50% align:center
<i>Tororo! Tororo!</i>

00:15:16.875 --> 00:15:20.128 position:50% align:center
[SOBA CLERK A]
Here we go. One <i>tororo</i> soba.

00:15:20.211 --> 00:15:22.756 position:50% align:center
Hey, what's your name, anyway?

00:15:22.839 --> 00:15:25.675 position:50% align:center
[KURENO]
Oh, right. Um, I'm Kureno.

00:15:25.759 --> 00:15:29.346 position:50% align:center
I'm Arisa Uotani.
Nice to meet you.

00:15:29.429 --> 00:15:31.681 position:50% align:center
So, what're you
doin' around here?

00:15:31.765 --> 00:15:34.100 position:50% align:center
Do you work in the
area or somethin'?

00:15:34.184 --> 00:15:37.437 position:50% align:center
Actually, I was just
sorta wandering.

00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:39.481 position:50% align:center
No destination in mind.

00:15:39.564 --> 00:15:42.067 position:50% align:center
And here's your
chicken <i>nanban</i> , sir.

00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:43.526 position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:15:43.610 --> 00:15:46.988 position:50% align:center
It's been awhile since I've
taken a break from work.

00:15:47.072 --> 00:15:52.285 position:50% align:center
I didn't know what else to do,
so I figured I'd go for a walk.

00:15:53.745 --> 00:15:55.038 position:50% align:center
Are you working today?

00:15:55.121 --> 00:15:59.542 position:50% align:center
Oh, um, yeah, I am.
At my second job, at a café.

00:15:59.626 --> 00:16:03.505 position:50% align:center
Well, I'm 26, but I'd guess
that you're in high school?

00:16:03.588 --> 00:16:04.339 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
A junior.

00:16:04.422 --> 00:16:05.924 position:50% align:center
Yet so independent.

00:16:06.007 --> 00:16:08.259 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Nah, it's nothing special.

00:16:08.343 --> 00:16:09.844 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Nine years older than me.

00:16:09.928 --> 00:16:12.722 position:50% align:center
That's a pretty decent age gap.

00:16:12.806 --> 00:16:14.140 position:50% align:center
I don't know.

00:16:14.224 --> 00:16:15.934 position:50% align:center
I can't even find my way
around a convenience store,

00:16:16.017 --> 00:16:18.228 position:50% align:center
and you work two jobs.

00:16:18.311 --> 00:16:20.730 position:50% align:center
I'd never been in one
before that night.

00:16:20.814 --> 00:16:22.607 position:50% align:center
Heh. It's kind of pathetic, huh?

00:16:22.691 --> 00:16:26.403 position:50% align:center
Okay, what's your deal? You a
celebrity or some kinda royalty?

00:16:26.486 --> 00:16:27.946 position:50% align:center
Uh, no. I'm not.

00:16:28.029 --> 00:16:29.572 position:50% align:center
How have you made it 26 years

00:16:29.656 --> 00:16:31.741 position:50% align:center
without ever going to
a convenience store?

00:16:31.825 --> 00:16:34.285 position:50% align:center
That's impossible. Come on!

00:16:34.369 --> 00:16:37.622 position:50% align:center
[KURENO]
I've never needed to.

00:16:37.706 --> 00:16:42.627 position:50% align:center
Going out to a store like that,
it was just a trivial errand,

00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:45.505 position:50% align:center
and I don't normally do those.

00:16:45.588 --> 00:16:50.343 position:50% align:center
I go about my life,
and I work. That's all.

00:16:50.427 --> 00:16:51.720 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Trivial?

00:16:51.803 --> 00:16:53.054 position:50% align:center
[KURENO
I guess you could say

00:16:53.138 --> 00:16:55.098 position:50% align:center
I've got a pretty
structured existence.

00:16:55.181 --> 00:16:57.267 position:50% align:center
Which is why I was a little lost

00:16:57.350 --> 00:16:59.769 position:50% align:center
when I found myself
with a day off.

00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:04.274 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] And you're happy?
Living that way?

00:17:04.357 --> 00:17:06.276 position:50% align:center
Why wouldn't I be?

00:17:06.359 --> 00:17:09.863 position:50% align:center
I have everything I need.
More than most.

00:17:09.946 --> 00:17:14.159 position:50% align:center
So, yes. I'm content.

00:17:16.369 --> 00:17:21.291 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] If that's true,
why is your smile so sad?

00:17:21.374 --> 00:17:25.378 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] Both today,
and that first night we met,

00:17:25.462 --> 00:17:29.549 position:50% align:center
I've noticed how
hollow his smile is.

00:17:30.759 --> 00:17:33.345 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] There's something
lonely about it.

00:17:34.929 --> 00:17:37.432 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
A trivial errand?

00:17:37.515 --> 00:17:39.559 position:50% align:center
That's all it was.

00:17:39.642 --> 00:17:42.562 position:50% align:center
And I guess that's all
this is, too, isn't it?

00:17:44.647 --> 00:17:49.235 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] Ever since that night,
I've wanted to see you again.

00:17:49.319 --> 00:17:52.322 position:50% align:center
And then, when I ran
into you before,

00:17:52.405 --> 00:17:58.828 position:50% align:center
and you said we should get lunch
together, it... it just...

00:17:58.912 --> 00:18:02.332 position:50% align:center
It made me feel
really happy! Okay?!

00:18:02.415 --> 00:18:05.210 position:50% align:center
This isn't trivial to me!

00:18:05.293 --> 00:18:07.796 position:50% align:center
Thanks for lunch. See ya.

00:18:13.593 --> 00:18:15.345 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Why am I so mad?

00:18:15.428 --> 00:18:18.223 position:50% align:center
I mean, he's just
some random guy.

00:18:18.306 --> 00:18:20.642 position:50% align:center
Sorry I wasted your time.

00:18:20.725 --> 00:18:23.061 position:50% align:center
Sorry you paid for my lunch.

00:18:23.144 --> 00:18:25.563 position:50% align:center
And I'm sorry I couldn't
make you smile

00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:28.483 position:50% align:center
like you really meant it.

00:18:28.566 --> 00:18:29.484 position:50% align:center
[KURENO]
Hold on!

00:18:29.567 --> 00:18:30.944 position:50% align:center
Arisa! Just wait!

00:18:31.027 --> 00:18:33.613 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow, we're on a first
name basis already?

00:18:33.697 --> 00:18:35.073 position:50% align:center
Slow down, please.

00:18:35.156 --> 00:18:37.117 position:50% align:center
Stop following me
like some stalker.

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:39.911 position:50% align:center
I am way to pissed off
to talk right now.

00:18:39.994 --> 00:18:41.830 position:50% align:center
I only need a minute.

00:18:41.913 --> 00:18:43.373 position:50% align:center
Please? Don't cry.

00:18:43.456 --> 00:18:45.000 position:50% align:center
I am not crying!

00:18:45.083 --> 00:18:48.294 position:50% align:center
[KURENO] I'm sorry. I swear
I didn't mean it that way.

00:18:48.378 --> 00:18:52.549 position:50% align:center
I was happy, too. Before.

00:18:52.632 --> 00:18:55.468 position:50% align:center
When I realized who you were.

00:18:55.552 --> 00:19:01.057 position:50% align:center
You chased after me in this heat
just for a chance to talk.

00:19:02.142 --> 00:19:05.145 position:50% align:center
Ever since that night...

00:19:05.228 --> 00:19:08.440 position:50% align:center
...I've been thinking about you.

00:19:08.523 --> 00:19:10.817 position:50% align:center
Wanting to see you again.

00:19:12.444 --> 00:19:13.862 position:50% align:center
Oh. You have?

00:19:13.945 --> 00:19:15.363 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI laughs]

00:19:15.447 --> 00:19:16.031 position:50% align:center
You're blushing.

00:19:16.114 --> 00:19:17.115 position:50% align:center
No, I'm not!

00:19:17.198 --> 00:19:18.658 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:19:20.326 --> 00:19:22.162 position:50% align:center
[KURENO]
Liar.

00:19:22.245 --> 00:19:24.164 position:50% align:center
[KURENO laughs]

00:19:25.790 --> 00:19:30.003 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
That's... a real smile.

00:19:53.234 --> 00:19:55.737 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
That look...

00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:57.739 position:50% align:center
And that touch...

00:19:57.822 --> 00:20:00.408 position:50% align:center
He felt something, too.

00:20:03.912 --> 00:20:05.538 position:50% align:center
[MEGUMI]
So how do you feel?

00:20:05.622 --> 00:20:07.957 position:50% align:center
Is he somebody you could
see yourself with?

00:20:08.041 --> 00:20:09.668 position:50% align:center
I have no idea.

00:20:09.751 --> 00:20:11.836 position:50% align:center
He's all mysterious
and confusing.

00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:13.797 position:50% align:center
Nothing he does makes any sense.

00:20:13.880 --> 00:20:16.883 position:50% align:center
I mean, why did he just
take off? That jerk.

00:20:16.966 --> 00:20:20.720 position:50% align:center
What, did I have <i>tororo</i>
breath or something?

00:20:20.804 --> 00:20:23.807 position:50% align:center
Could it be that...
he's married?

00:20:23.890 --> 00:20:24.974 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Oh, man.

00:20:25.058 --> 00:20:27.894 position:50% align:center
Whole thing was bull
if that's the case.

00:20:27.977 --> 00:20:29.396 position:50% align:center
Well, whatever.

00:20:29.479 --> 00:20:32.941 position:50% align:center
I probably won't talk to him
again unless he comes to me.

00:20:33.024 --> 00:20:35.443 position:50% align:center
Guess we'll see what happens.

00:20:35.527 --> 00:20:37.320 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:20:37.404 --> 00:20:39.864 position:50% align:center
Are you lonely?

00:20:39.948 --> 00:20:41.574 position:50% align:center
I'll be all right.

00:20:41.658 --> 00:20:43.159 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Hanajima.

00:20:43.243 --> 00:20:44.911 position:50% align:center
If Tohru ever gets a boyfriend,

00:20:44.994 --> 00:20:47.372 position:50% align:center
we're totally crashing
their first date.

00:20:47.455 --> 00:20:50.583 position:50% align:center
One hundred percent.

00:20:50.667 --> 00:20:52.919 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHARU]
Ginger pork. Yay.

00:20:53.003 --> 00:20:54.254 position:50% align:center
Leave already.

00:20:54.337 --> 00:20:55.880 position:50% align:center
I'm next, right?

00:20:55.964 --> 00:20:57.257 position:50% align:center
Meat! Yum!

00:20:57.340 --> 00:20:58.925 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU] We should have
enough for seconds, too.

00:20:59.009 --> 00:21:01.636 position:50% align:center
So, what'd you do for
your first afternoon off?

00:21:01.720 --> 00:21:03.304 position:50% align:center
